MediSort AI – Smart Medical Waste Classification

An AI-powered system for real-time biomedical waste detection and classification in hospitals.
Data is processed with Python (TensorFlow/Keras, OpenCV) and visualized via Streamlit for an interactive web interface.

<img width="1000" height="429" alt="MediSort Output" src="assets/output_placeholder.png" />
Overview

MediSort AI consolidates biomedical waste data and images into a single view for hospital staff.
The system automates classification of waste into Hazardous, Chemical, and Non-Hazardous categories, reducing human exposure and improving operational efficiency.

Key Features

Real-time waste classification via CNN-based model

Automatic alerts for hazardous waste detection (optional SMS/email)

Confidence score display for each classification

User-friendly interface with image/video upload

Scalable for integration with IoT-enabled bins and robotic handling

Technology

Python (TensorFlow/Keras, OpenCV) – image preprocessing, CNN model training, prediction

Streamlit – interactive web interface

NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib, Pillow – data handling and visualization

Insights from the System

Hazardous waste detection is highly accurate (~95–98% confidence)

Reduces manual handling, minimizing health risks for staff

Supports safe and compliant biomedical waste segregation

System is adaptable to different lighting conditions, cluttered backgrounds, and varied waste types

Confidence scores allow staff to verify classification reliability before disposal
